19/03/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Interior Ministry announced on Sunday (March 18th) it has been investigating 19 police officers from the Delchevo border checkpoint for corruption. 
The ministry has found over 25 cases in which the officers allegedly accepted bribes in exchange for allowing overloaded trucks to enter the country. 
The news agency Focus reports that 15 other police and customs officers were arrested at the weekend in a separate operation targeting corruption in public institutions. 
(Makfax, A1 TV, Focus - 18/03/07)
